- desc: 'Functions and constants to access the window, window event listeners

    and screen dimming.'
  members:
  - desc: Sets a window event listener.
    name: set_listener
    parameters:
    - desc: 'A callback which receives info about window events. Pass an empty function
        or nil if you no longer wish to receive callbacks.


        `self`

        : [type:object] The calling script


        `event`

        : [type:constant] The type of event. Can be one of these:


        - `window.WINDOW_EVENT_FOCUS_LOST`

        - `window.WINDOW_EVENT_FOCUS_GAINED`

        - `window.WINDOW_EVENT_RESIZED`

        - `window.WINDOW_EVENT_ICONIFIED`

        - `window.WINDOW_EVENT_DEICONIFIED`


        `data`

        : [type:table] The callback value `data` is a table which currently holds
        these values


        - [type:number] `width`: The width of a resize event. nil otherwise.

        - [type:number] `height`: The height of a resize event. nil otherwise.'
      name: callback
      type: function(self, event, data)
    type: function
  - desc: 'Set the locking state for current mouse cursor on a PC platform.


      This function locks or unlocks the mouse cursor to the center point of the window.
      While the cursor is locked,

      mouse position updates will still be sent to the scripts as usual.'
    name: set_mouse_lock
    parameters:
    - desc: The lock state for the mouse cursor
      name: flag
      type: boolean
    type: function
  - desc: '[icon:ios] [icon:android] Sets the dimming mode on a mobile device.


      The dimming mode specifies whether or not a mobile device should dim the screen
      after a period without user interaction. The dimming mode will only affect the
      mobile device while the game is in focus on the device, but not when the game
      is running in the background.


      This function has no effect on platforms that does not support dimming.'
    name: set_dim_mode
    parameters:
    - desc: 'The mode for screen dimming


        - `window.DIMMING_ON`

        - `window.DIMMING_OFF`'
      name: mode
      type: constant
    type: function
  - desc: '[icon:ios] [icon:android] Returns the current dimming mode set on a mobile
      device.


      The dimming mode specifies whether or not a mobile device should dim the screen
      after a period without user interaction.


      On platforms that does not support dimming, `window.DIMMING_UNKNOWN` is always
      returned.'
    name: get_dim_mode
    parameters: []
    returns:
    - desc: 'The mode for screen dimming


        - `window.DIMMING_UNKNOWN`

        - `window.DIMMING_ON`

        - `window.DIMMING_OFF`'
      type: constant
    type: function
  - desc: This returns the current window size (width and height).
    name: get_size
    parameters: []
    returns:
    - desc: The window width
      type: number
    - desc: The window height
      type: number
    type: function
  - desc: This returns the current lock state of the mouse cursor
    name: get_mouse_lock
    parameters: []
    returns:
    - desc: The lock state
      type: boolean
    type: function
  - desc: This event is sent to a window event listener when the game window or app
      screen has lost focus.
    name: WINDOW_EVENT_FOCUS_LOST
    type: number
  - desc: 'This event is sent to a window event listener when the game window or app
      screen has

      gained focus.

      This event is also sent at game startup and the engine gives focus to the game.'
    name: WINDOW_EVENT_FOCUS_GAINED
    type: number
  - desc: 'This event is sent to a window event listener when the game window or app
      screen is resized.

      The new size is passed along in the data field to the event listener.'
    name: WINDOW_EVENT_RESIZED
    type: number
  - desc: '[icon:osx] [icon:windows] [icon:linux] This event is sent to a window event
      listener when the game window or app screen is

      iconified (reduced to an application icon in a toolbar, application tray or
      similar).'
    name: WINDOW_EVENT_ICONFIED
    type: number
  - desc: '[icon:osx] [icon:windows] [icon:linux] This event is sent to a window event
      listener when the game window or app screen is

      restored after being iconified.'
    name: WINDOW_EVENT_DEICONIFIED
    type: number
  - desc: Dimming mode is used to control whether or not a mobile device should dim
      the screen after a period without user interaction.
    name: DIMMING_ON
    type: number
  - desc: Dimming mode is used to control whether or not a mobile device should dim
      the screen after a period without user interaction.
    name: DIMMING_OFF
    type: number
  - desc: 'Dimming mode is used to control whether or not a mobile device should dim
      the screen after a period without user interaction.

      This mode indicates that the dim mode can''t be determined, or that the platform
      doesn''t support dimming.'
    name: DIMMING_UNKNOWN
    type: number
  name: window
  type: table
